
[1]evasion

   EVA'SION, n. s as z. [L. evasio, from evado, evasi. See Evade.]

   The act of eluding or avoiding, or of escaping, particularly from the
   pressure of an argument, from an accusation or charge, from an
   interrogatory and the like; excuse; subterfuge; equivocation; artifice
   to elude; shift. Evasion of a direct answer weakens the testimony of a
   witness.

   Thou by evasions thy crime uncover'st more.
